Printing Error 11B (0x0000011B) – Explanation for Exam Purpose
1. Introduction
Printing Error 0x0000011B (commonly called Error 11B) is a well-known issue in Windows that started appearing after certain security updates. It mainly affects network printing, where users are unable to connect to shared printers or print documents.
2. What is Printing Error 11B?
It is a network printing error that occurs when a user tries to connect to a shared printer.
The error message usually appears as:
👉 “Windows cannot connect to the printer. Operation failed with error 0x0000011B.”
It prevents users from accessing printers shared over a network.
3. Cause of Error 0x0000011B
The error was caused by security updates released by Microsoft.
These updates were introduced to fix vulnerabilities like PrintNightmare.
The update enforced stricter RPC (Remote Procedure Call) authentication between client and print server.
Main Reasons
Mismatch in authentication levels between client and server
Older systems not supporting new security requirements
Misconfigured network printer settings
4. How the Error Occurs (Working)
A user tries to connect to a shared network printer
The system attempts to communicate with the print server
Due to stricter security rules, the connection fails
The system displays Error 0x0000011B
5. Impact of the Error
Users cannot print over the network
Shared printers become inaccessible
Affects offices, schools, and organizations
Causes workflow disruption
6. How the Error Was Resolved
(a) Microsoft Updates and Fixes
Microsoft released additional updates to fix compatibility issues
Improved handling of RPC authentication
(b) Registry Modification (Temporary Fix)
Administrators added a registry key to relax authentication:
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\Print
RpcAuthnLevelPrivacyEnabled = 0
This allowed systems to connect to printers again
⚠️ Note: This was a temporary workaround and reduced security
(c) Updating All Systems
Ensuring both client and print server have the latest updates
Maintains compatibility and security
(d) Reconfiguring Printer Settings
Reinstalling shared printers
Updating printer drivers
Ensuring proper network configuration
(e) Using Secure Printing Practices
Enforcing proper authentication settings
Avoiding outdated systems
7. Prevention Measures
Keep Windows systems fully updated
Use latest printer drivers
Ensure proper network configuration
Avoid disabling security features permanently
Maintain consistency across client and server systems
